trying to prove that phan is real is like toying with a potential of outing people. not that a single phannie has a lot of influence and credibility on their own, but when a bunch of them gather their ‘evidence’ and publicly present it for the whole internet to see, they all but say 'hey, onision/shane dawson/random bottom-feeding drama channel! look! here’s some material for ur new video! use phan for attention!’. this was especially relevant a few years ago, but it’s still something that implies that to phannies, outing people is a fun game they play as a hobby. you’re both wasting your time AND doing something morally wrong. 

case in point, here’s a clip of dan being a more decent person than a typical member of his fanbase:

just don’t try to ‘prove’ anything, appreciate those two as people, and re-read this more often if you really can’t live without a reminder:

body:
5 + 1 bus AU

Person A goes home by the same bus every day. They’re not in a good place in life right now and they just constantly feel down, exhausted after a long day of work/school/whatever. Person B goes by the same bus every day. After some time B notices A(a sad person sitting alone at the end of the bus) and starts smiling at them to somehow make them feel better? And it works. Person B smiles at A and A smiles back and it’s the highlight of A’s day. Until one day B isn’t smiling. B sits down alone at the end of the bus and tries to smile at A, but just,,, can’t. So A sits next to B and wordlessly hugs them. B starts crying and tells A what’s wrong. This is the first time they talk.

Or, 5 times B helped A and 1 time A helped B.

(Please, if you write anything inspired by this, link it in the notes)
